&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>I love these books.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Hellboy, Vol. 4: The Right Hand of Doom</title><link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/15/hellboy-vol.-4-the-right-hand-of-doom/</link><pubDate>Wed, 15 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/15/hellboy-vol.-4-the-right-hand-of-doom/</guid><description>&lt;figure class="cover-image">
&lt;a data-goodreads-type="book" data-goodreads-id="102460" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/102460.hellboy-vol-4-the-right-hand-of-doom">&lt;img src="https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/hellboy-vol-4-the-right-hand-of-doom.jpg">&lt;/a>
&lt;/figure>
&lt;blockquote>
&lt;p>One day someone at Dark Horse asked if I was interested in doing a story about young Hellboy. I wasn&amp;rsquo;t, but instead of saying no I said, &amp;ldquo;What about two pages of Hellboy eating pcancakes?&amp;rdquo; I thought it was a riot. I didn&amp;rsquo;t expect anyone else to like it, but it turned out to be a big hit with a lot of readers. It&amp;rsquo;s nice when that happens.&lt;/p>
&lt;/blockquote>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/attachments/hellboy-4-pancakes.png" alt="Hellboy-4-Pancakes">&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Hellboy, Vol. 3: The Chained Coffin and Others</title><link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/14/hellboy-vol.-3-the-chained-coffin-and-others/</link><pubDate>Tue, 14 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/14/hellboy-vol.-3-the-chained-coffin-and-others/</guid><description>&lt;figure class="cover-image">
&lt;a data-goodreads-type="book" data-goodreads-id="102461" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/102461.hellboy-vol-3-the-chained-coffin-and-others">&lt;img src="https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/hellboy-vol-3-the-chained-coffin-and-others.jpg">&lt;/a>
&lt;/figure>
&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://blog.jverkamp.com/embeds/books/attachments/hellboy-3-weird-fruit.png" alt="Hellboy-3-Weird-fruit">&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Well that was a weird tonal shift. After two books&lt;sup id="fnref:1">&lt;a href="#fn:1" class="footnote-ref" role="doc-noteref">1&lt;/a>&lt;/sup> chock full of Nazis and demonic imagery and larger worldbuilding, &lt;a data-goodreads-type="book" data-goodreads-id="102461" href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/102461.hellboy-vol-3-the-chained-coffin-and-others">Hellboy, Vol. 3: The Chained Coffin and Others&lt;/a> basically feels like a number of short stories all told in the Hellboy universe.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Hellboy, Vol. 2: Wake the Devil</title><link>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/11/hellboy-vol.-2-wake-the-devil/</link><pubDate>Sat, 11 Apr 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://blog.jverkamp.com/2020/04/11/hellboy-vol.-2-wake-the-devil/</guid><description>&lt;figure class="cover-image">
